Contains a list of Regular expressions based on the provided inputs. RegexPatternSet can be used with other WAF entities with RegexPatternSetReferenceStatement to perform other actions .


{{% examples %}}

## Example Usage

{{< chooser language "typescript,python,go,csharp" / >}}


### Example


{{< example csharp >}}

```csharp
using Pulumi;
using AwsNative = Pulumi.AwsNative;

class MyStack : Stack
{
    public MyStack()
    {
        var exampleRegexPatternSet = new AwsNative.WAFv2.RegexPatternSet("exampleRegexPatternSet", new AwsNative.WAFv2.RegexPatternSetArgs
        {
            Name = "ExampleRegexPatternSet",
            Scope = "REGIONAL",
            Description = "This is an example RegexPatternSet",
            RegularExpressionList = 
            {
                "^foobar$",
                "^example$",
            },
        });
    }

}

```


{{< /example >}}


{{< example go >}}


```go
package main

import (
	"fmt"

	"github.com/pulumi/pulumi-aws-native/sdk/go/aws/wafv2"
	"github.com/pulumi/pulumi/sdk/v3/go/pulumi"
)

func main() {
	pulumi.Run(func(ctx *pulumi.Context) error {
		_, err := wafv2.NewRegexPatternSet(ctx, "exampleRegexPatternSet", &wafv2.RegexPatternSetArgs{
			Name:        pulumi.String("ExampleRegexPatternSet"),
			Scope:       "REGIONAL",
			Description: pulumi.String("This is an example RegexPatternSet"),
			RegularExpressionList: pulumi.StringArray{
				pulumi.String(fmt.Sprintf("%v%v", "^foobar", "$")),
				pulumi.String(fmt.Sprintf("%v%v", "^example", "$")),
			},
		})
		if err != nil {
			return err
		}
		return nil
	})
}

```
